Screening List for School Visitors 








April 21, 2020
Sangre Community,
In a meeting with Governor Polis and CDE's Katy Anthes, we have been informed that we will not return to in person learning for the remainder of the 2019-20 school year. Remote learning will continue until further notice. Please have your students reaching out to their teachers if they need anything. We will keep you updated with any changes. As always, stay safe, let us know if we can help in any way, and if you have any questions, please contact Mr. Stagner.
March 19th, 2020
Dear Parents,
March 18th, 2020 our Board of Education voted to close our school due to the COVID-19 outbreak. This decision was based on what is best for our students, parents, staff and community. School will resume at a yet to be determined date.
We are still planning on providing our students with core instruction in hopes of keeping them from falling behind academically. This will be done via virtual instruction and communication between student, parent and instructor. The plan is to have this accessible to all of our students by Wed. March 25th.
The key to success will be communication. We are meeting with our staff on Monday to make final plans. Our wishes are to make this as lease stressful on you, your children and our staff.
Please understand that this instruction will look very differently from in the past. We will do our best in helping your children progressing academically.
At this time, we ask you to be patient and continue to look for information via our website and or messaging system.
Sincerely,
Brady Stagner
Sangre de Cristo Superintendent





Welcome to Sangre De Cristo Schools!
School District Mission:
The Sangre de Cristo School District shall strive to provide a safe environment for all students and staff while offering meaningful opportunities of innovative educational programs for all students which challenge every student to:
Develop their full academic and social potential including the attainment of content standards and be prepared to make competent decisions in our changing world through partnerships between home, school and community.
To achieve this mission, students, teachers, administrators, parents, and community members must work together guided by the three R’s: Rights, Respect, and Responsibilities.


